definition: first of the ten Heavenly Stems 十天干[shi2 tian1 gan1]/(used for an unspecified person or thing)/first (in a list, as a party to a contract etc)/letter "A" or roman "I" in list "A, B, C", or "I, II, III" etc/armor plating/shell or carapace/(of the fingers or toes) nail/bladed leather or metal armor (old)/ranking system used in the Imperial examinations (old)/civil administration unit in the baojia 保甲[bao3 jia3] system (old)/ancient Chinese compass point: 75°

sentences.english: Copepods are small and funny looking one eyed crustaceans.
sentences.chinese: 橈足類是尋找一個有趣的小眼睛的甲殼類動物。

sentences.english: A decapod crustacean has ten limbs.
sentences.chinese: 十足蟲甲殼類動物喲十隻足肢。

sentences.english: With the trash of carapace aquatic product as the calcium source, calcium propionate is produced by the synthesis of propionic acid and acid.

sentences.english: The number of shelled creatures in the ocean is truly dizzying.
sentences.chinese: 海洋中的甲殼類生物的數量真的很多。

sentences.english: Old World genus of isopod crustaceans.
sentences.chinese: 陸生等足甲殼類舊大陸鼠婦科的一屬。

sentences.english: These garishly colored crustaceans are favorites of the aquarium trade.
